India Equity: Emmsons International, Marico, Sun Pharmaceutical

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-04-11T10:54:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/india-equity-jk-paper-idea-cellular-nitesh-estate-suzlon.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share levels are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai. The
markets are closed tomorrow for a public holiday.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
188.91, or 1 percent, to 19,262.54, its fifth straight session
of decline. The BSE 200 Index retreated 0.9 percent to 2,380.04.  Emmsons International Ltd. (EMSI)   slid 3.7 percent to
87.6 rupees. The food grains exporter’s vessel carrying rice
cargo, worth $6.9 million, from  Pakistan  to  Bangladesh  met with
an accident at Chittagong port, according to a statement to the
Bombay Stock Exchange on April 8.  Hindustan Zinc Ltd. (HZ)   rose 1.8 percent to a record
146.25 rupees. India’s largest producer raised prices by 0.7
percent to 123,700 rupees a metric ton today, according to the
company’s website.  Marico Ltd. (MRCO)  , the maker of hair-care products,
surged 7 percent to a record 147.9 rupees, as some investors
sought companies that are less vulnerable to an increase in
borrowing costs and a slowdown in industrial output. About 2
million shares changed hands today, more than three times the
three-month daily average.        Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (SUNP)   jumped 2
percent to 450.4 rupees. The nation’s biggest drugmaker by
market value may partner with Merck & Co. to sell the second-
biggest U.S. drug company’s products in India, the Mint
reported, citing two people aware of the development.  -- Editor: Ravil Shirodkar  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai at 
